annotation.TEXT: Ooh, boy. I've already spent over 400 of my 500 seconds! Better get my butt in gear!
Well, it looks like the enemies are subject to the wrap-around as well.
Now, do I use the P-switch here?
Well, I think I'm doing a good job of killing everything.

That part of the terrain hitting the top of the screen should've been made solid flooring all the way across to prevent the player from falling through like that. I always wonder how level designers overlook such obvious flaws...
Well, surely I can reach it with a max speed jump...
Come on, get in that pipe...
Well, that was me being dumb.
I'm going to keep trying at ludicrous speed for a moment here.
Just back here, and... Oh, duh. I just figured out how to make that jump to reach the springboard.
Since that was "science" though, I've gone and rewound time there, so that death never happened.
Ack! I'm glad that didn't kill me.
Huh. This isn't Cave Story music. It's actually Sonic CD - Stardust Speedway Good Future (Japanese/PAL soundtrack). (Thanks for telling me what it is, 8azaz22!)
Oh, and in case you weren't paying attention in the first few seconds, this hack was made by Klopenator. Also, it was requested for me to play by moster87654321.
Hey, it made my springboard disappear in a puff of smoke!
Nothing? Oh wait, there's something. Ah, now I clearly see how to get the key!

And that warps me over here, where I can slide-kill some goombas. If that's how this was meant to work, there should've been a ceiling of some sort to prevent me from jumping over the top and falling to my death before.
Wait, what? Where'd my "bigness" go? I know I finished that level super...
Well, there's a springboard up there, and a YI-style door. Anything more to the right?
Ah, slaying all of the enemies turned it into a real wall triangle! Neat.
Huh? Listen to the music here. What's it doing?
Okay, whatever.
Of course, it's so obvious.
So, I guess I'll be taking on The Big Fish next time! To be continued...
Ha! I was expecting the yellow koopa to jump there!
Now, I wonder where I should use this P-switch...
Oh, a P-switch. Well, I suppose I take that back to the other room and use it somewhere there.
Yeah, it does. Dang it! It's like the hack maker knew I'd try that!
Yep, just as I thought. It's a wrap-around level.
Darn it! I keep falling short! Maybe if I try jumping from the blocks on the left?
In fact, let's do some "science" here...
Heh, the locked door conceals the springboard.
More Cave Story music. Okay, so I guess that's gonna be a running theme here, which I have no problem with. So, I've got two levels to pick from... Let's start with Mario's Temp. House.

Okay, I've had enough. I'm tired of trying to hit that message box right now, so let's just save that for later. There'll probably be a point where the game will provide the means for me to read it, so nobody spoil what it says right now!
"Take all the enemies' lives", eh? Well, that's something I should be good at!
Hey, wasn't this pipe orange to begin with? Heh, it's just like in the original game's Donut Secret 1.

Alright, forget it. I'm wasting too much time there. So, let's go to Puzzle Island, and I'll come back for that message box later. (I'll be able to reach it for sure if I encounter any power ups or a Yoshi.)
Yep, just as I thought. It's possible to "teleport" into something solid and get killed.
Whoops! That's the problem with trying to put the wrap-around effect in SMW. It's never as clean as in SMB2 and SMB3, instead making Mario appear to just suddenly teleport.
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and I've decided which hack I'll play next...
Well, back to ludicrous speed...
We've got "Running Hell" playing in the background, which I guess fits this level well.

Science count: 1

Anything down here?

Let's just quickly verify something...
Stickerbrush Symphony? That's definitely not a Cave Story tune.
I wonder why that one ledge is way over there?
Oh, I'm so going to beat that fish down alright!
It's "The Big Fish Chrisis"! The extra "H" stands for "Huge". That's how big a fish and how big a crisis it is!
"Find the exit before time runs out!" And it's giving me 500 seconds, so now I'm worried about the scope of these puzzles...
Well, that's the fifth Yoshi coin, so I've gotta be almost done...
Oh, yeah. I've gotta kill that slow Pokey.

Whoops! I'm occasionally accidentally exiting the level.

Let's get another reserve mushroom, just in case.
